AWKA – An Onitsha High Court, pre­sided over by Hon. Justice D.A. Onyefulu on Wednesday sentenced two youths, Valen­tine Umezinwa and Emeka Okolonji to death for murder of a sex worker, Blessing Eze. Delivering the judgment Justice Onyefulu said he had listened to the cross-examina­tion by the State Counsel, N. S. Emeka, and the response from the prison officials who testi­fied of the good conduct of the accused during their period in correctional facilities. The Judge had earlier reject­ed the plea by their Counsel on the ground of youthful exuber­ance, saying that if that should be allowed to stand youth would be acting irresponsibly and wasting people’s lives Mutilated Body Of Middle Aged With One Year Free Health Services… Afikpo Community Elders Move To Checkmate Cult Activities The mother of Emeka Okolonji had wept bitterly in court saying that her son who had been nursing an ambition to study abroad had never been found with bad gang. Justice Onyefulu said that the Counsel to the convicts have the option of appeal as well as through the committee of prerogative of mercy stress­ing that the Governor has the final say on the matter though he said the counsel have not shown enough reason why jus­tice should be tampered with mercy. State Counsel, N. S. Emeka, while speaking to the press on the judgment said that justice has been done to the deceased, to the state and to the convicts, stressing that the convicts have the right to appeal over the judg­ment. The defence Counsel, C. C. Okeke said they received the judgment with open heart stressing that they will ap­proach the committee for the prerogative of mercy, and will also appeal on the judgment It will be recalled that the convicts were accused of mur­dering one Blessing Eze, a sex worker, whom they lured, mur­dered and dumped the corpse around Dennis Memorial Grammar School, Onitsha.